<title type="html"><![CDATA[How much text can a nintendo cart handle?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1520&amp;p=13002#p13002"><![CDATA[
Yeah, you could do this using a simple NROM-128 cart. It uses only 16kb of ROM, but that's enough to hold the 12000+ characters and you'll still have nearly 4kb to write the program. Since all the program does is display the text, it is not very complex and will easily fit in that space.<br /><br />I believe that NROM-128 is the smallest kind of cart you'll find. That means your program could fit in whatever cart you find. But there is no reason to get complicated with mappers and such, so try to stick to NROM-128 or NROM-256.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue May 16, 2006 12:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
